-- South African Coal Export Prices Increase to Highest in a Month
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-08-06T09:12:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/south-african-coal-export-prices-increase-to-highest-in-a-month.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
Richards Bay, the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, increased the most in a month.  Coal for  immediate delivery  rose $2.90, or 3.4 percent, to
$88.52 a metric ton in the week ended Aug. 3, according to IHS
McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the highest level since July
6, 2012. The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
